==English==

===Verb===
'''[[wash]] [[out]]'''
#To [[remove]] something by [[washing]].
#:''That stain will easily '''wash out'''.''
# {{idiom}} To [[wear]] away by the [[flow]] of [[water]]; to [[erode]].
#:''The sandcastle was '''washed out''' by the tide.
#{{idiom}} To be [[depleted]] of [[energy]].
#:''After all this editing, I feel '''washed out'''.''
#{{idiom}} To [[cancel]] due to bad [[weather]].
#:''The continuous rain '''washed out''' the cricket match.''

